    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI see that multi cursor is on the road map for 0.12. one thing that has been on mind in this respect is how close the \":normal\" comes to being a solution to multi cursor.\n\nThe big problem with \":normal\" when compared to canonical multi cursor is that it is not interactive. You cannot see the immediate effect of what the motions you are typing are.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nincnormal is as incsearch is to \"/\". It would add immediate visual feedback to the \":normal\" command.",
