            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This is already possible with a plugin via `:help :command-preview` , that was its purpose. https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/18194\n\nHowever, there are tricky situations with `:normal`, it's essentially equivalent to executing potentially unfinished, destructive commands at any step.\n\n`nvim_parse_cmd` is very useful for that, but we don't yet have an equivalent for normal-mode commands.",
